Wash and dry produce.

Dice @tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and very thinly slice @shallot{1}. Mince @garlic{1%clove}. Halve @lemon{1}. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; chop leaves into bite-size pieces. Trim and halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons.

== Marinated Tomato ==

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together half the @Greek vinaigrette{1.5%oz}, 1 TBSP olive oil, ¼ tsp @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tbsp}, and ½ tsp @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil, ½ tsp Tuscan Heat Spice, and 1 tsp sugar.

Add tomato and as much shallot as you like; toss to coat. Set aside to marinate.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with remaining Tuscan Heat Spice, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

== Lemon Tahini Dressing ==

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine garlic, juice from whole lemon (two lemons for 4 servings), @tahini{4%tbsp}, remaining Greek vinaigrette, and 1 TBSP olive oil. Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time until dressing reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil.

== Assembly ==

To bowl with marinated tomato, add lettuce and cucumber; toss until thoroughly coated.

Divide salad between plates; top with chicken. Drizzle with dressing and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.